editorialSummary.text: Upbeat, modern spot dispensing familiar coffee house fare such as paninis and pastries.

originalText.text:
Atmosphere: The cafe has a relaxed and inviting atmosphere, with plenty of seating both indoors and outdoors. It's a great place to people-watch or simply enjoy a cup of coffee and a snack.
Service: The staff were friendly and prompt, and they were happy to make recommendations.
Food and drinks: The food and drinks are all made fresh to order, and the quality is excellent. I especially liked the bagels, which were large and delicious. The orange juice was also fresh and flavorful.
Value for money: The prices are reasonable for the quality of the food and drinks. I would definitely recommend Sip n Co. to anyone looking for a great place to enjoy a coffee or pastry.
Overall, I had a very positive experience at Sip n Co. and would definitely recommend it to others.

originalText.text:
I headed here on a very briskly and warm Wednesday after a doctor‚Äôs appointment I had, I was on a facetime call with a close friend and she was helping me chose which cafe I should head to. Together we stumbled upon this cafe.

Absolutely beautiful and charming little cafe, right south of central park, about a block away so a little walk to the park was perfect! They serve a nice wide range of sweets and savoury items, and cooling tasty beverages.

I‚Äôve read and heard much about Sip + Co‚Äôs coffee, but sadly I didn‚Äôt get to try that since I already had my daily dose of caffeine, but instead i grabbed one of their specialty lemonades being the passionfruit lemonade! I got that with some cookies, being the Tahini cooke, and a chocolate and lemon  crinkle. Absolutely delicious and hit exactly what i needed to hit my sweet tooth on that day, I will have to say that I‚Äôm absolutely in love with their lemonade, very enticing and sourly sweet!

Their customer service was very friendly and engaging, the barista was quite talkative too which made my experience even better! Also i just wanted to add about the whole atmosphere of this small local cafe, very warm and cozy.

I'd definitely go back to this place and recommend it to my friends because of the enriching cookies and lemonade!

P.S it‚Äôs a perfect little treat to have while you‚Äôre reading your favorite book in central park, so don‚Äôt miss out!
